# =============================================================================
# Trivy Security Scan — Accepted Vulnerabilities
# =============================================================================
# These CVEs are known and accepted risks. Each has been evaluated and
# documented with a justification for why it is not immediately fixable.
#
# Review this file periodically and remove entries when fixes are available.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Starlette DoS Vulnerabilities (transitive dependency via FastAPI)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# fastapi ^0.109.0 depends on starlette 0.36.3 which cannot be independently
# upgraded without breaking the FastAPI version constraint.
# Upgrading FastAPI to a version that depends on starlette >=0.40.0 requires
# API changes and is tracked for the next major update cycle.
# Risk assessment: LOW — the server is not public-facing (internal IoT backend).

# CVE-2024-24762: ReDoS via malformed Content-Type header in multipart form data
# Severity: HIGH (CVSS 7.5) | Fixed in starlette >=0.36.2 (but needs FastAPI upgrade)
CVE-2024-24762

# CVE-2024-47874: DoS via unbounded multipart form field buffering
# Severity: HIGH (CVSS 8.7) | Fixed in starlette >=0.40.0
CVE-2024-47874
